cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.IR, cs.GR, cs.NE 

The paper deals with image fusion, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The specific application is in microscopical images, which falls under the sub-category of multimedia (cs.MM). The paper also discusses the use of speed-up robust features (SURF), which is a popular feature detection algorithm used in image retrieval (cs.IR) and graphics (cs.GR). Finally, the paper proposes a method for integrating information from multiple images, which is a common problem in neural networks (cs.NE).
